# SBCRM — Keep Docs in Sync

Whenever you add, change, or remove a feature, field, component, UI element, or behaviour in this project, you MUST update both documentation files **in the same commit**:

- `DOCUMENTATION.md` — technical reference (fields, components, constants, architecture)
- `USER_GUIDE.md` — plain-language end-user guide (how to use the feature, step-by-step)

## What triggers a doc update

| Change type | DOCUMENTATION.md | USER_GUIDE.md |
|---|---|---|
| New section / nav item | Add full section with fields table, views, requirements | Add how-to steps in plain language |
| New field on a record | Add row to the schema table for that section | Update "what to enter" instructions if user-facing |
| New view or tab | Document layout, columns, and filters | Explain when and how to use it |
| New component | Add to the component table in Technical Architecture | Add to relevant user-facing section |
| Changed status values or dropdown options | Update the values in the relevant fields table | Update status definition table for users |
| Security or auth change | Update Authentication & Security section | Update Logging In / Profile sections |
| Removed feature | Remove from both docs | Remove from both docs |

## Where to add new sections

- **DOCUMENTATION.md**: Insert between the last feature section and "Navigation & Layout". Update the Table of Contents numbering.
- **USER_GUIDE.md**: Insert in logical usage order (before "Your Profile"). Update the Table of Contents numbering.

## Style rules

- DOCUMENTATION.md: Technical, precise, uses tables and field listings.
- USER_GUIDE.md: Plain language, no jargon, uses numbered steps and friendly explanations.
- Both: Keep the existing formatting style. Do not add emojis unless already present.
